com.solacesystems.solclientj.core.handle

Interface ReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Handle

    public interface ReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle
extends Handle
    The ReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle interface allows applications to serialize a ReplicationGroupMessageId object into a ReplicationGroupMessageId formatted String, compare ReplicationGroupMessageId objects and validate ReplicationGroupMessageId objects in the Native API.

    Applications that need this interface must instantiate an object with the ReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle interface by calling Allocator.newReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle(). To deserialize ReplicationGroupMessageId formatted String into an allocated ReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle object, applications must call Solclient.createReplicationGroupMessageIdForHandle()

    The ReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle can also be received from the ReplicationGroupMessageId in the message by calling getReplicationGroupMessageIdForHandle(ReplicationGroupMessageIdHandle)
